00:08:08.420 --> 00:08:10.730 align:middle line:84%
I live fairly close
to him in the UK.

00:08:10.730 --> 00:08:12.110 align:middle line:90%
Off I went to his studio.

00:08:12.110 --> 00:08:14.750 align:middle line:84%
Met this amazing
celebrity, and then we're

00:08:14.750 --> 00:08:15.830 align:middle line:90%
suddenly in the studio.

00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:17.930 align:middle line:84%
And it's a very
humorous interview

00:08:17.930 --> 00:08:19.880 align:middle line:84%
actually because
he's kind of going

00:08:19.880 --> 00:08:22.820 align:middle line:84%
at it from the science and
the skeptical point of view.

00:08:22.820 --> 00:08:25.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm sort of saying,
well, I believe,

00:08:25.340 --> 00:08:28.157 align:middle line:84%
in quoting Patrick Swayze
from "Ghost," I have no idea.

00:08:28.157 --> 00:08:29.990 align:middle line:84%
And by the end of the
interview, we actually

00:08:29.990 --> 00:08:31.430 align:middle line:90%
really are on the same page.

00:08:31.430 --> 00:08:33.830 align:middle line:84%
It's a lovely journey
of an interview.

00:08:33.830 --> 00:08:35.960 align:middle line:84%
But the section about
dreams, we talk about it,

00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:37.789 align:middle line:84%
and he says he doesn't like
dreaming because he only

00:08:37.789 --> 00:08:38.589 align:middle line:90%
has nightmares.

00:08:38.589 --> 00:08:39.950 align:middle line:90%
So I'll go into nightmares.

00:08:39.950 --> 00:08:42.350 align:middle line:84%
Nightmares are
transformative gifts

00:08:42.350 --> 00:08:44.690 align:middle line:84%
because when we
have a nightmare,

00:08:44.690 --> 00:08:47.600 align:middle line:84%
it's kind of your dreaming
mind sending tough love

00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:50.870 align:middle line:84%
because the gentle other
non-nightmare dreams haven't

00:08:50.870 --> 00:08:51.800 align:middle line:90%
got through.

00:08:51.800 --> 00:08:53.450 align:middle line:84%
The message hasn't
got through, so they

00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:56.263 align:middle line:84%
need to send you shocking
content to wake you up.

00:08:56.263 --> 00:08:58.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, it's sort of
like a-- many people I've

00:08:58.430 --> 00:09:00.530 align:middle line:84%
interviewed had to have
a near-death experience,

00:09:00.530 --> 00:09:02.330 align:middle line:84%
get into a car
accident or something,

00:09:02.330 --> 00:09:05.100 align:middle line:84%
to awaken their abilities
or to recognize them.

00:09:05.100 --> 00:09:08.075 align:middle line:84%
So this is the version of that
at night where you're dreaming.

00:09:08.075 --> 00:09:08.875 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:09:08.875 --> 00:09:10.042 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: I say in my books.

00:09:10.042 --> 00:09:12.830 align:middle line:84%
Our dreams are a nocturnal
therapist and far cheaper

00:09:12.830 --> 00:09:14.000 align:middle line:90%
than a real one.

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:17.720 align:middle line:84%
Every night we have this
self-healing process going on,

00:09:17.720 --> 00:09:19.340 align:middle line:84%
where our dreaming
mind is sending us,

00:09:19.340 --> 00:09:22.580 align:middle line:84%
through language of symbols
and metaphors, images for us

00:09:22.580 --> 00:09:26.270 align:middle line:84%
to brainstorm about ways to
improve, and heal, and move

00:09:26.270 --> 00:09:27.650 align:middle line:90%
forward in our waking life.

00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:29.870 align:middle line:84%
If only we realize
the priceless gift

00:09:29.870 --> 00:09:31.970 align:middle line:84%
that we've got there
every single night,

00:09:31.970 --> 00:09:34.830 align:middle line:84%
and nightmares are important
because we meet our shadow

00:09:34.830 --> 00:09:35.630 align:middle line:90%
side.

00:09:35.630 --> 00:09:36.547 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:09:36.547 --> 00:09:38.630 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: And our shadow
side is very important

00:09:38.630 --> 00:09:40.400 align:middle line:84%
because most of us
in our waking life

00:09:40.400 --> 00:09:42.270 align:middle line:90%
like to repress or deny that.

00:09:42.270 --> 00:09:44.390 align:middle line:84%
However, just as
there's day and night,

00:09:44.390 --> 00:09:46.790 align:middle line:84%
there's shadow and
light within us all.

00:09:46.790 --> 00:09:50.720 align:middle line:84%
And we have to face
that, understand it,

00:09:50.720 --> 00:09:53.210 align:middle line:84%
love it, and then
in our waking life,

00:09:53.210 --> 00:09:56.480 align:middle line:84%
know that the potential to be
toxic and negative is within us

00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:59.870 align:middle line:84%
but have the moral courage to
choose to do the right thing.

00:09:59.870 --> 00:10:03.080 align:middle line:84%
It's that wonderful quote
about that story about the two

00:10:03.080 --> 00:10:06.320 align:middle line:84%
wolves within us, one that's
compassionate, and loving,

00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:09.002 align:middle line:84%
and kind and the other
that is toxic and negative.

00:10:09.002 --> 00:10:11.210 align:middle line:84%
And the little boy asks the
elder of the tribe, well,

00:10:11.210 --> 00:10:12.770 align:middle line:90%
which wolf wins this battle?

00:10:12.770 --> 00:10:15.560 align:middle line:84%
And the elder says, well,
the one you choose to feed.

00:10:15.560 --> 00:10:17.990 align:middle line:84%
So nightmares are
showing us that side,

00:10:17.990 --> 00:10:20.930 align:middle line:84%
saying you've got it within
you so that when you wake up,

00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:23.000 align:middle line:90%
choose the right thing.

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:24.410 align:middle line:90%
That's real moral courage.

00:10:24.410 --> 00:10:26.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
the best explanation

00:10:26.390 --> 00:10:28.310 align:middle line:84%
I've ever heard about
it because when I do

00:10:28.310 --> 00:10:30.260 align:middle line:84%
think of that corollary
of daytime hours--

00:10:30.260 --> 00:10:32.690 align:middle line:84%
and so many people
I've interviewed here

00:10:32.690 --> 00:10:34.940 align:middle line:84%
have gone through these
really rough experiences--

00:10:34.940 --> 00:10:36.650 align:middle line:84%
and then I woke up
and realized what

00:10:36.650 --> 00:10:38.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm supposed to do
and to see that that's

00:10:38.780 --> 00:10:42.590 align:middle line:84%
accessible to everyone every
day if they do have nightmares.

00:10:42.590 --> 00:10:45.320 align:middle line:84%
And this is on kind
of a sliding scale.

00:10:45.320 --> 00:10:47.938 align:middle line:84%
There are nightmares, and then
there are nightmares, you know?

00:10:47.938 --> 00:10:49.730 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: And nightmares,
it's safe as well

00:10:49.730 --> 00:10:51.480 align:middle line:84%
because, obviously,
with our shadow side,

00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:54.260 align:middle line:84%
we can't go around cheating,
and lying, and murdering,

00:10:54.260 --> 00:10:56.990 align:middle line:84%
and being serial
killers in our--

00:10:56.990 --> 00:10:58.490 align:middle line:84%
you've got to
respect other people.

00:10:58.490 --> 00:11:01.770 align:middle line:84%
But we can safely role play,
get it all out of our system.

00:11:01.770 --> 00:11:03.020 align:middle line:90%
It's very cathartic.

00:11:03.020 --> 00:11:06.620 align:middle line:84%
In the nightmare, you can be the
most toxic version of yourself,

00:11:06.620 --> 00:11:08.990 align:middle line:84%
understand it, know
that-- and also

00:11:08.990 --> 00:11:11.360 align:middle line:84%
kind of try to understand
why it's there.

00:11:11.360 --> 00:11:14.960 align:middle line:84%
And I call it the golden shadow,
where you heal and embrace

00:11:14.960 --> 00:11:17.780 align:middle line:84%
that part of you as well,
because sometimes our shadow

00:11:17.780 --> 00:11:20.840 align:middle line:84%
side does force us
to grow and evolve

00:11:20.840 --> 00:11:23.930 align:middle line:84%
because if we're always
blissful and always harmonious,

00:11:23.930 --> 00:11:25.970 align:middle line:84%
growth doesn't tend
to happen there.

00:11:25.970 --> 00:11:28.340 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we need
to get comfortable

00:11:28.340 --> 00:11:31.530 align:middle line:84%
being uncomfortable because
that makes us evolve.

00:11:31.530 --> 00:11:33.650 align:middle line:84%
And I think from
all the research

00:11:33.650 --> 00:11:37.160 align:middle line:84%
I've done, that the meaning
of our lives is to evolve.

00:11:37.160 --> 00:11:38.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with you.

00:11:38.300 --> 00:11:38.840 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:11:38.840 --> 00:11:40.730 align:middle line:84%
And everyone's on a
different trajectory,

00:11:40.730 --> 00:11:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and it takes a different
stimuli for each person

00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:46.850 align:middle line:84%
to be able to accomplish
that, and the willingness

00:11:46.850 --> 00:11:48.920 align:middle line:84%
to embrace it, take it
on, and learn from it.

00:11:48.920 --> 00:11:51.200 align:middle line:84%
So often, these gifts
are just floating by,

00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:52.190 align:middle line:90%
and we don't see them.

00:11:52.190 --> 00:11:52.550 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Yes.

00:11:52.550 --> 00:11:54.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So I was going
to tell you something funny

00:11:54.140 --> 00:11:55.140 align:middle line:90%
because it's on my mind.

00:11:55.140 --> 00:11:57.620 align:middle line:84%
It's a dream I had just
before waking up this morning.

00:11:57.620 --> 00:12:00.770 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- and I would love
for you to play with it a bit

00:12:00.770 --> 00:12:02.930 align:middle line:84%
because I think it
can be interpreted

00:12:02.930 --> 00:12:05.810 align:middle line:84%
a couple of different ways,
right, in terms of the psyche.

00:12:05.810 --> 00:12:08.120 align:middle line:84%
So I'll make it
brief, but we have

00:12:08.120 --> 00:12:11.360 align:middle line:84%
a birth coming in our
family, a new little nephew.

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:13.670 align:middle line:84%
My sister's child,
the son, and his wife

00:12:13.670 --> 00:12:16.205 align:middle line:84%
are having a baby soon,
so that must have been

00:12:16.205 --> 00:12:17.330 align:middle line:90%
what was in the background.

00:12:17.330 --> 00:12:20.330 align:middle line:84%
So the baby's here,
and the baby's

00:12:20.330 --> 00:12:21.920 align:middle line:90%
being held by his grandfather.

00:12:21.920 --> 00:12:26.120 align:middle line:84%
And his grandfather has this
spiky, punky gray hair, right?

00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:28.860 align:middle line:84%
And the baby comes out with
spiky, punky gray hair.

00:12:28.860 --> 00:12:31.340 align:middle line:84%
So I'm looking at the little
baby and thinking, wow,

00:12:31.340 --> 00:12:33.710 align:middle line:84%
I don't think I've ever seen
a full head of gray hair

00:12:33.710 --> 00:12:35.300 align:middle line:90%
on a newborn.

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:36.390 align:middle line:90%
It was very funny.

00:12:36.390 --> 00:12:39.350 align:middle line:84%
But then I realized, because
I had the dream again,

00:12:39.350 --> 00:12:42.260 align:middle line:84%
I thought I woke up and was
telling my sister the dream,

00:12:42.260 --> 00:12:43.710 align:middle line:90%
but I had the dream again.

00:12:43.710 --> 00:12:46.863 align:middle line:84%
Said you've got to know
this little baby is for him.

00:12:46.863 --> 00:12:47.780 align:middle line:90%
It's for your husband.

00:12:47.780 --> 00:12:49.220 align:middle line:90%
It's for Norbert.

00:12:49.220 --> 00:12:52.460 align:middle line:84%
This is his love bond
is this new baby coming.

00:12:52.460 --> 00:12:55.275 align:middle line:84%
And so I did call my sister
when I actually woke up,

00:12:55.275 --> 00:12:56.900 align:middle line:84%
and she's like, oh
my god, I love this.

00:12:56.900 --> 00:13:00.510 align:middle line:84%
So on that level, that can be
a couple of different things.

00:13:00.510 --> 00:13:01.310 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: It can.

00:13:01.310 --> 00:13:02.480 align:middle line:90%
There's so much to unpick there.

00:13:02.480 --> 00:13:02.960 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Regina.

00:13:02.960 --> 00:13:04.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Don't spend too much
time on it because we have

00:13:04.400 --> 00:13:05.240 align:middle line:90%
way--

00:13:05.240 --> 00:13:06.323 align:middle line:90%
many more dreams to go to.

00:13:06.323 --> 00:13:07.700 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: But I'm so excited.

00:13:07.700 --> 00:13:11.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, 99% of our
dreams, over 99%,

00:13:11.030 --> 00:13:14.450 align:middle line:84%
are symbolic, metaphorical,
where our dreaming mind

00:13:14.450 --> 00:13:17.210 align:middle line:84%
is picking up on things in our
waking life that we've missed

00:13:17.210 --> 00:13:21.090 align:middle line:84%
and then, in our dreams, shows
us in that symbolic language

00:13:21.090 --> 00:13:21.890 align:middle line:90%
that dreams love.

00:13:21.890 --> 00:13:23.900 align:middle line:84%
Our dreaming mind is
an artist, a visionary.

00:13:23.900 --> 00:13:25.373 align:middle line:90%
It speaks like a poet.

00:13:25.373 --> 00:13:26.540 align:middle line:90%
We can talk more about that.

00:13:26.540 --> 00:13:28.580 align:middle line:84%
But there is a tiny
percentage of dreams--

00:13:28.580 --> 00:13:30.680 align:middle line:84%
and I've written many
books about this--

00:13:30.680 --> 00:13:32.390 align:middle line:90%
that are kind of paranormal.

00:13:32.390 --> 00:13:34.310 align:middle line:84%
And this dream could
well fall into that.

00:13:34.310 --> 00:13:36.980 align:middle line:84%
You woke up with a strong
sense that you were dreaming

00:13:36.980 --> 00:13:38.210 align:middle line:90%
on behalf of someone else.

00:13:38.210 --> 00:13:39.742 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, it
seemed very clear.

00:13:39.742 --> 00:13:42.200 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Well, it makes sense
because in your waking life,

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:43.430 align:middle line:90%
you are like an oracle.

00:13:43.430 --> 00:13:45.680 align:middle line:84%
You probably do a lot on
behalf of other people.

00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:46.940 align:middle line:90%
You're very highly intuitive.

00:13:46.940 --> 00:13:49.160 align:middle line:84%
You couldn't do what
you're doing so well

00:13:49.160 --> 00:13:50.870 align:middle line:90%
without that intuitive ability.

00:13:50.870 --> 00:13:53.750 align:middle line:84%
So of course, as I say, our
waking and our sleeping life

00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:54.710 align:middle line:90%
are connected.

00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:56.855 align:middle line:84%
In your dreams,
your consciousness,

00:13:56.855 --> 00:13:58.730 align:middle line:84%
your spirit, soul,
whatever you want to call,

00:13:58.730 --> 00:14:00.620 align:middle line:90%
is continuing to work.

00:14:00.620 --> 00:14:02.540 align:middle line:90%
You're working in your dreams.

00:14:02.540 --> 00:14:04.160 align:middle line:90%
We call them sleepworker dreams.

00:14:04.160 --> 00:14:05.750 align:middle line:90%
And I find them very beautiful.

00:14:05.750 --> 00:14:08.600 align:middle line:84%
And that is a message
for your loved

00:14:08.600 --> 00:14:12.980 align:middle line:84%
one about this baby bringing
wisdom, bringing growth.

00:14:12.980 --> 00:14:14.840 align:middle line:84%
The gray hair is
wisdom and growth.

00:14:14.840 --> 00:14:16.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you could
also look at it

00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:18.710 align:middle line:84%
personally because there
is a theory of dreams

00:14:18.710 --> 00:14:20.427 align:middle line:84%
that every time you
dream like that movie

00:14:20.427 --> 00:14:21.635 align:middle line:90%
"Inception," when everybody--

00:14:21.635 --> 00:14:22.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Amazing dream.

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:23.210 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:14:23.210 --> 00:14:23.660 align:middle line:90%
I mean, amazing film.

00:14:23.660 --> 00:14:25.910 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --looks at the
dreamer that you are dreaming

00:14:25.910 --> 00:14:28.020 align:middle line:90%
about aspects of yourself.

00:14:28.020 --> 00:14:31.970 align:middle line:84%
And I would say, in your
work, that you are presenting

00:14:31.970 --> 00:14:35.630 align:middle line:84%
ancient, timeless wisdom and
constantly reinventing it

00:14:35.630 --> 00:14:36.680 align:middle line:90%
in a new way.

00:14:36.680 --> 00:14:37.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Baby with gray hair.

00:14:37.940 --> 00:14:38.330 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Yeah.

00:14:38.330 --> 00:14:39.747 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
so that would-- it

00:14:39.747 --> 00:14:42.290 align:middle line:84%
sounds like both are very
well true in that one.

00:14:42.290 --> 00:14:43.850 align:middle line:84%
And for my version
of a nightmare,

00:14:43.850 --> 00:14:45.980 align:middle line:84%
and it is when I went
up to say something

00:14:45.980 --> 00:14:48.770 align:middle line:84%
to the grandpa who
was guardedly holding

00:14:48.770 --> 00:14:51.830 align:middle line:84%
the little gray-haired baby,
he said something snippy.

00:14:51.830 --> 00:14:53.630 align:middle line:84%
That's about as bad
as my dreams get.

00:14:53.630 --> 00:14:55.130 align:middle line:90%
I had my feelings hurt a little.

00:14:55.130 --> 00:14:56.210 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:56.210 --> 00:14:57.440 align:middle line:90%
That's a nightmare for me.

00:14:57.440 --> 00:14:59.820 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Oh, so no
serial killer nightmares.

00:14:59.820 --> 00:15:00.012 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:15:00.012 --> 00:15:00.110 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:15:00.110 --> 00:15:00.530 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:15:00.530 --> 00:15:01.410 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: No zombies
or vampires--

00:15:01.410 --> 00:15:02.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Somebody
saying something snippy,

00:15:02.990 --> 00:15:03.740 align:middle line:90%
and it's like, oh.

00:15:03.740 --> 00:15:05.210 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --or stuck
in mud, suffocating.

00:15:05.210 --> 00:15:05.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:15:05.960 --> 00:15:06.110 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:15:06.110 --> 00:15:06.320 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:06.410 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: These are top dreams.

00:15:06.410 --> 00:15:07.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: None of that.

00:15:07.820 --> 00:15:10.490 align:middle line:90%
Just joking, but that is true.

00:15:10.490 --> 00:15:11.708 align:middle line:90%
So that's interesting.

00:15:11.708 --> 00:15:13.250 align:middle line:84%
So we can take these,
and we can look

00:15:13.250 --> 00:15:15.350 align:middle line:84%
at different elements
depending because many

00:15:15.350 --> 00:15:17.570 align:middle line:84%
of the people in this
audience are very intuitive,

00:15:17.570 --> 00:15:20.183 align:middle line:84%
are probably also dreaming
on behalf of others.

00:15:20.183 --> 00:15:22.100 align:middle line:84%
So that's why it's nice
to be able to break it

00:15:22.100 --> 00:15:24.110 align:middle line:90%
down so beautifully both ways.

00:15:24.110 --> 00:15:25.340 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Absolutely.

00:15:25.340 --> 00:15:28.930 align:middle line:84%
The ancient Greek oracles
would dream incubation,

00:15:28.930 --> 00:15:30.680 align:middle line:84%
where people would go
with their problems,

00:15:30.680 --> 00:15:31.992 align:middle line:90%
and then the oracle's there.

00:15:31.992 --> 00:15:33.700 align:middle line:84%
Maybe in another life
that was what you--

00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:35.210 align:middle line:90%
you would dream on it.

00:15:35.210 --> 00:15:36.650 align:middle line:84%
And I do know
actually some people

00:15:36.650 --> 00:15:38.430 align:middle line:84%
who dream on behalf
of other people.

00:15:38.430 --> 00:15:39.380 align:middle line:90%
That's what they do.

00:15:39.380 --> 00:15:41.000 align:middle line:84%
I think it's utterly
beautiful, and I

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:42.620 align:middle line:84%
get-- people write
to me all the time,

00:15:42.620 --> 00:15:44.203 align:middle line:84%
and I get so many
stories about people

00:15:44.203 --> 00:15:47.000 align:middle line:84%
who have dreamed of being at
the passing of a loved one when

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:49.080 align:middle line:84%
they didn't know that
loved one had departed.

00:15:49.080 --> 00:15:49.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:15:49.970 --> 00:15:52.040 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Incredible data, that.

00:15:52.040 --> 00:15:53.276 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, they're there.

00:15:53.276 --> 00:15:54.195 align:middle line:90%
They're a witness.

00:15:54.195 --> 00:15:56.570 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: How, in spirit,
holding their hand to help them

00:15:56.570 --> 00:15:57.140 align:middle line:90%
over the--

00:15:57.140 --> 00:15:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's beautiful.

00:15:57.590 --> 00:15:59.585 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --bridge to the other
side, whatever that may be.

00:15:59.585 --> 00:16:01.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You alluded to
something a little bit ago.

00:16:01.620 --> 00:16:03.078 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like to
pick back up on it,

00:16:03.078 --> 00:16:05.480 align:middle line:84%
and that is that
dreaming really started

00:16:05.480 --> 00:16:09.020 align:middle line:84%
coming to the forefront
more during the pandemic.

00:16:09.020 --> 00:16:12.260 align:middle line:84%
What I'm curious about is
because so much fear was

00:16:12.260 --> 00:16:16.720 align:middle line:84%
perpetuated during waking
hours during the pandemic,

00:16:16.720 --> 00:16:21.280 align:middle line:84%
how did that seem to affect
the content or quality of dream

00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:22.090 align:middle line:90%
time for people?

00:16:22.090 --> 00:16:23.620 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Well,
basically, I mean,

00:16:23.620 --> 00:16:25.682 align:middle line:84%
people got more sleep if
they were on furlough,

00:16:25.682 --> 00:16:27.640 align:middle line:84%
so their mornings were
slower, giving more time

00:16:27.640 --> 00:16:28.480 align:middle line:90%
for dream recall.

00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:30.850 align:middle line:84%
They also probably got more
REM, rapid eye movement,

00:16:30.850 --> 00:16:31.650 align:middle line:90%
stage sleep.

00:16:31.650 --> 00:16:34.390 align:middle line:90%
So that's the rational reason.

00:16:34.390 --> 00:16:36.592 align:middle line:84%
But the spiritual,
psychological reason

00:16:36.592 --> 00:16:38.050 align:middle line:84%
is that dreams were
doing what they

00:16:38.050 --> 00:16:42.490 align:middle line:84%
do best, which is trying to
help, and heal us, and show us

00:16:42.490 --> 00:16:45.520 align:middle line:84%
that this was an unprecedented
opportunity for us to fall

00:16:45.520 --> 00:16:48.227 align:middle line:84%
in love with our inner
world, our inner psychic.

00:16:48.227 --> 00:16:49.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very true.

00:16:49.060 --> 00:16:52.810 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: And that was why this
unleashing of dreams happen.

00:16:52.810 --> 00:16:54.250 align:middle line:90%
And I am testament to that.

00:16:54.250 --> 00:16:57.040 align:middle line:84%
As I said, I've been
writing about dream decoding

00:16:57.040 --> 00:17:00.970 align:middle line:84%
and the power of our
night vision for decades.

00:17:00.970 --> 00:17:03.460 align:middle line:84%
But it's only been in the
last two to three years

00:17:03.460 --> 00:17:04.420 align:middle line:90%
that I have suddenly--

00:17:04.420 --> 00:17:06.819 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've had my
readership and my following,

00:17:06.819 --> 00:17:09.040 align:middle line:84%
but I've gone on
mainstream platforms,

00:17:09.040 --> 00:17:12.010 align:middle line:84%
as I say, all over the world,
including the likes of Capital

00:17:12.010 --> 00:17:15.880 align:middle line:84%
Radio, to dream decode for
celebrities because everybody

00:17:15.880 --> 00:17:17.290 align:middle line:90%
is having these dreams.

00:17:17.290 --> 00:17:20.230 align:middle line:84%
And I hope, as we move
away from the pandemic,

00:17:20.230 --> 00:17:22.480 align:middle line:84%
that we don't lose
our connection

00:17:22.480 --> 00:17:23.410 align:middle line:90%
to our dreaming mind.

00:17:23.410 --> 00:17:24.285 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I hope not.

00:17:24.285 --> 00:17:25.869 align:middle line:84%
But maybe this
was a breakthrough

00:17:25.869 --> 00:17:28.240 align:middle line:84%
in terms of mass
consciousness because you also

00:17:28.240 --> 00:17:32.645 align:middle line:84%
told me off camera that
you're now showing on--

00:17:32.645 --> 00:17:33.445 align:middle line:90%
did you say ITV?

00:17:33.445 --> 00:17:34.690 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: ITV this morning.

00:17:34.690 --> 00:17:35.035 align:middle line:90%
Viewer call-ins.

00:17:35.035 --> 00:17:35.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: ITV.

00:17:35.380 --> 00:17:35.920 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:17:35.920 --> 00:17:36.580 align:middle line:90%
So you hear--

00:17:36.580 --> 00:17:36.910 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Never.

00:17:36.910 --> 00:17:37.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:17:37.710 --> 00:17:38.965 align:middle line:90%
And this is mainstream TV.

00:17:38.965 --> 00:17:39.765 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Yes.

00:17:39.765 --> 00:17:43.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they have you on
decoding dreams and paranormal

00:17:43.810 --> 00:17:45.650 align:middle line:90%
phenomena for the public.

00:17:45.650 --> 00:17:50.380 align:middle line:84%
Now that's a big step to
acknowledge this and feed

00:17:50.380 --> 00:17:52.885 align:middle line:84%
that part of their
audience on mainstream.

00:17:52.885 --> 00:17:55.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: I've learned over
the years that going on there

00:17:55.840 --> 00:17:59.140 align:middle line:84%
talking about psychic
animals or life after death,

00:17:59.140 --> 00:18:02.403 align:middle line:84%
mainstream can't go
there, especially the UK,

00:18:02.403 --> 00:18:03.445 align:middle line:90%
which is very skeptical--

00:18:03.445 --> 00:18:04.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, very.

00:18:04.160 --> 00:18:04.993 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: --the BBC.

00:18:04.993 --> 00:18:09.485 align:middle line:84%
However, when it's dreaming,
it's like they don't mind.

00:18:09.485 --> 00:18:11.860 align:middle line:84%
But what they don't realize
when I'm going on there dream

00:18:11.860 --> 00:18:15.340 align:middle line:84%
decoding, I'm actually
talking about spirituality,

00:18:15.340 --> 00:18:16.570 align:middle line:90%
that invisible world.

00:18:16.570 --> 00:18:20.140 align:middle line:84%
And I've learned now that's
the way forward for me,

00:18:20.140 --> 00:18:22.180 align:middle line:84%
to go on there and
dream decode for really

00:18:22.180 --> 00:18:23.980 align:middle line:84%
big celebrities over in the
UK that I've done before.

00:18:23.980 --> 00:18:25.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because
it's OK to dream.

00:18:25.050 --> 00:18:26.710 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: It's OK
because we all dream.

00:18:26.710 --> 00:18:27.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:18:27.510 --> 00:18:30.460 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: And even the
most skeptical person still

00:18:30.460 --> 00:18:33.760 align:middle line:84%
has had a weird dream that they
don't know what the meaning is,

00:18:33.760 --> 00:18:36.340 align:middle line:84%
and they want me to tell them
and help them understand.

00:18:36.340 --> 00:18:39.580 align:middle line:84%
And then I explain to them it's
a bit like nocturnal therapy.

00:18:39.580 --> 00:18:42.010 align:middle line:84%
Where is this invisible
world that we go to?

00:18:42.010 --> 00:18:43.570 align:middle line:90%
Isn't it fun dreaming?

00:18:43.570 --> 00:18:45.590 align:middle line:84%
It's like all these light
bulbs are going off.

00:18:45.590 --> 00:18:47.950 align:middle line:84%
And I love it because
dreams are a portal.

00:18:47.950 --> 00:18:50.920 align:middle line:84%
They're the first step
to awakening people

00:18:50.920 --> 00:18:54.190 align:middle line:84%
to this incredible world of
mind, body, spirit out there.

00:18:54.190 --> 00:18:55.720 align:middle line:90%
And long may it continue.

00:18:55.720 --> 00:18:58.480 align:middle line:84%
And I must say that the
Millennial generation

00:18:58.480 --> 00:19:00.575 align:middle line:84%
are particularly interested
in their dreaming.

00:19:00.575 --> 00:19:01.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, really?

00:19:01.450 --> 00:19:02.380 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: It seems
a lot of them,

00:19:02.380 --> 00:19:04.338 align:middle line:84%
the pandemic has done
that, that all the things

00:19:04.338 --> 00:19:06.850 align:middle line:84%
they used to rely on,
like their social media

00:19:06.850 --> 00:19:09.910 align:middle line:84%
following, or the
career, or money,

00:19:09.910 --> 00:19:12.460 align:middle line:84%
or looks to give
them sustenance, that

00:19:12.460 --> 00:19:14.290 align:middle line:84%
clearly doesn't in
times like that when

00:19:14.290 --> 00:19:15.550 align:middle line:90%
your health is threatened.

00:19:15.550 --> 00:19:18.700 align:middle line:84%
But they found sustenance
through understanding

00:19:18.700 --> 00:19:20.260 align:middle line:84%
their dreaming
life is important.

00:19:20.260 --> 00:19:21.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you know
this because more of them

00:19:21.370 --> 00:19:22.630 align:middle line:90%
started reaching out to you.

00:19:22.630 --> 00:19:23.020 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Yes.

00:19:23.020 --> 00:19:25.020 align:middle line:84%
Well, books like "Night
Vision," which what I've

00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:26.280 align:middle line:90%
done for the younger--

00:19:26.280 --> 00:19:27.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, I love it.

00:19:27.280 --> 00:19:28.810 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --people
who are new to this--

00:19:28.810 --> 00:19:30.643 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, that's
what I loved about it.

00:19:30.643 --> 00:19:32.710 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was so
beautiful, especially,

00:19:32.710 --> 00:19:34.450 align:middle line:84%
like you say, for
people who have just

00:19:34.450 --> 00:19:36.867 align:middle line:84%
started awakening to the notion
they should pay attention.

00:19:36.867 --> 00:19:38.680 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Yeah, and
there's an unparalleled

00:19:38.680 --> 00:19:41.470 align:middle line:84%
interested in astrology
at the moment as well.

00:19:41.470 --> 00:19:44.260 align:middle line:84%
I've done astrological profiles
for all the royal family

00:19:44.260 --> 00:19:48.410 align:middle line:84%
in the UK, with major
national newspapers, including

00:19:48.410 --> 00:19:51.355 align:middle line:84%
our prime minister and the
leader of the opposition.

00:19:51.355 --> 00:19:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And can you believe that
a national newspaper

00:19:53.230 --> 00:19:55.720 align:middle line:84%
has asked me to give them a
psychological profile based

00:19:55.720 --> 00:19:56.595 align:middle line:90%
on date of birth?

00:19:56.595 --> 00:19:58.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:19:58.000 --> 00:19:59.250 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] I love it.

