to have a more intimate
relationship with their clients

00:23:36.200 --> 00:23:39.910 align:middle line:84%
and help them get the right
skincare or beauty product.

00:23:39.910 --> 00:23:41.770 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
absolutely fascinating.

00:23:41.770 --> 00:23:43.480 align:middle line:84%
When I listen to
it-- well, we can

00:23:43.480 --> 00:23:44.900 align:middle line:90%
go a lot of directions on that.

00:23:44.900 --> 00:23:49.060 align:middle line:84%
But what I want to do is go
back for a moment to what you

00:23:49.060 --> 00:23:51.760 align:middle line:84%
were talking about when
all of this information

00:23:51.760 --> 00:23:53.650 align:middle line:84%
starts pouring through
your dream time,

00:23:53.650 --> 00:23:57.160 align:middle line:84%
and there's a particular
element that you've picked up

00:23:57.160 --> 00:23:59.890 align:middle line:84%
on during the day or in
something you've watched,

00:23:59.890 --> 00:24:02.175 align:middle line:84%
and we tend to think,
oh, that's random.

00:24:02.175 --> 00:24:03.550 align:middle line:84%
You're saying
quite the opposite.

00:24:03.550 --> 00:24:05.860 align:middle line:84%
That's not remotely
random that your brain

00:24:05.860 --> 00:24:07.450 align:middle line:90%
picked that particular item.

00:24:07.450 --> 00:24:08.830 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Nothing is random.

00:24:08.830 --> 00:24:12.940 align:middle line:84%
Your dreaming mind is
super, super clever.

00:24:12.940 --> 00:24:14.620 align:middle line:84%
But the trouble is
most people give up

00:24:14.620 --> 00:24:16.120 align:middle line:90%
because it doesn't make sense.

00:24:16.120 --> 00:24:16.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:24:16.540 --> 00:24:18.010 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: So then I
encourage them, go and read--

00:24:18.010 --> 00:24:19.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They can't
find a context for it.

00:24:19.010 --> 00:24:20.968 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Go and read
Coleridge's "Kubla Khan."

00:24:20.968 --> 00:24:23.530 align:middle line:84%
"In Xanadu did Kubla Khan, a
stately pleasure dome decree,

00:24:23.530 --> 00:24:25.730 align:middle line:90%
where--" I know that backwards.

00:24:25.730 --> 00:24:28.750 align:middle line:90%
I used it so many times.

00:24:28.750 --> 00:24:32.303 align:middle line:84%
Go and read poetry that doesn't
make sense on first reading.

00:24:32.303 --> 00:24:33.220 align:middle line:90%
You have to unpick it.

00:24:33.220 --> 00:24:34.180 align:middle line:90%
We have to go back to school.

00:24:34.180 --> 00:24:35.752 align:middle line:84%
Like in your
literature classes, you

00:24:35.752 --> 00:24:37.210 align:middle line:84%
were taught about
pathetic fallacy.

00:24:37.210 --> 00:24:39.400 align:middle line:84%
You were taught about
symbols, metaphors, puns.

00:24:39.400 --> 00:24:41.800 align:middle line:90%
The dreaming mind loves puns.

00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:45.970 align:middle line:84%
And what it's encouraging you
to do is to become more creative

00:24:45.970 --> 00:24:48.280 align:middle line:84%
and to brainstorm
around a symbol.

00:24:48.280 --> 00:24:50.110 align:middle line:90%
What are the associations?

00:24:50.110 --> 00:24:52.035 align:middle line:84%
Again, I compare it
to a work of art.

00:24:52.035 --> 00:24:53.410 align:middle line:84%
There are some
great works of art

00:24:53.410 --> 00:24:56.360 align:middle line:84%
that you can stand and gaze
in awe at because there's

00:24:56.360 --> 00:24:57.160 align:middle line:90%
so much meaning--

00:24:57.160 --> 00:24:58.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:24:58.090 --> 00:24:58.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --because
you can say, well,

00:24:58.960 --> 00:25:00.100 align:middle line:84%
why isn't the dreaming
mind more obvious?

00:25:00.100 --> 00:25:02.350 align:middle line:84%
Because a picture, and
a poem, and a symbol

00:25:02.350 --> 00:25:06.280 align:middle line:84%
says so much more for you
than just words ever can.

00:25:06.280 --> 00:25:09.440 align:middle line:84%
And it wants you to see
that this is so much bigger.

00:25:09.440 --> 00:25:12.700 align:middle line:84%
There's so many more
expansive connections for you.

00:25:12.700 --> 00:25:15.910 align:middle line:84%
It wants you to think
like a poet, a visionary.

00:25:15.910 --> 00:25:17.450 align:middle line:90%
That's what it wants you to do.

00:25:17.450 --> 00:25:21.940 align:middle line:84%
So go to an art gallery, read
poetry, watch amazing movies.

00:25:21.940 --> 00:25:24.350 align:middle line:84%
Of course, big shout out
for "Inception," my favorite

00:25:24.350 --> 00:25:24.540 align:middle line:90%
movie--

00:25:24.540 --> 00:25:25.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, me too.

00:25:25.520 --> 00:25:26.320 align:middle line:90%
Big shout.

00:25:26.320 --> 00:25:27.748 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --because they show
you the potential and they

00:25:27.748 --> 00:25:27.820 align:middle line:90%
get--

00:25:27.820 --> 00:25:29.868 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The layers,
the dimensions of dream.

00:25:29.868 --> 00:25:31.910 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: And the symbolic
language it speaks in.

00:25:31.910 --> 00:25:33.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it's beautiful.

00:25:33.810 --> 00:25:35.920 align:middle line:84%
OK, now you just
triggered something in me.

00:25:35.920 --> 00:25:37.900 align:middle line:84%
So you have all
these people coming

00:25:37.900 --> 00:25:41.230 align:middle line:84%
to you who are looking
at how to begin

00:25:41.230 --> 00:25:45.145 align:middle line:84%
utilizing dreams in order, for
example, to sell their product.

00:25:45.145 --> 00:25:47.860 align:middle line:90%


00:25:47.860 --> 00:25:51.010 align:middle line:84%
Why can't that same faculty
be used to manipulate people

00:25:51.010 --> 00:25:52.375 align:middle line:90%
from other places?

00:25:52.375 --> 00:25:53.750 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Well,
I would hope not.

00:25:53.750 --> 00:25:56.050 align:middle line:84%
I hope that people would
do it with integrity.

00:25:56.050 --> 00:25:58.060 align:middle line:84%
But you've got to
understand, I--

00:25:58.060 --> 00:26:00.880 align:middle line:84%
one of the things when
I'm teaching companies

00:26:00.880 --> 00:26:04.000 align:middle line:84%
or whatever how to help with
dream decoding for clients

00:26:04.000 --> 00:26:06.460 align:middle line:84%
is to say you've always
got to say the best

00:26:06.460 --> 00:26:08.590 align:middle line:84%
person to interpret your
dreams is always you.

00:26:08.590 --> 00:26:09.790 align:middle line:90%
It's personal.

00:26:09.790 --> 00:26:11.090 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you example.

00:26:11.090 --> 00:26:13.150 align:middle line:84%
If I dream of a
dog, I love dogs.

00:26:13.150 --> 00:26:15.760 align:middle line:90%
It's a beautiful loving symbol.

00:26:15.760 --> 00:26:18.010 align:middle line:84%
However, if somebody had
an unfortunate experience

00:26:18.010 --> 00:26:21.200 align:middle line:84%
with a dog, although,
in my dream dictionary

00:26:21.200 --> 00:26:23.240 align:middle line:84%
it will say very positive
things about dogs--

00:26:23.240 --> 00:26:25.310 align:middle line:84%
unconditional love,
companionship-- however,

00:26:25.310 --> 00:26:27.260 align:middle line:84%
if you have had
personal association

00:26:27.260 --> 00:26:29.162 align:middle line:84%
with a dog that
is unpleasant, it

00:26:29.162 --> 00:26:30.620 align:middle line:84%
will have a very
different meaning.

00:26:30.620 --> 00:26:31.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:26:31.420 --> 00:26:34.310 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: So always go with
your own personal gut instinct

00:26:34.310 --> 00:26:35.510 align:middle line:90%
first about a symbol.

00:26:35.510 --> 00:26:37.220 align:middle line:84%
My dream dictionaries,
et cetera,

00:26:37.220 --> 00:26:41.443 align:middle line:84%
are the universal
common ways that we

00:26:41.443 --> 00:26:43.110 align:middle line:84%
think of these symbols
that kick start--

00:26:43.110 --> 00:26:44.568 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you
still suggest you

00:26:44.568 --> 00:26:46.953 align:middle line:84%
have to go in and see what
that feels like for you.

00:26:46.953 --> 00:26:49.370 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: But a lot of us have
lost touch with the ability

00:26:49.370 --> 00:26:50.773 align:middle line:90%
to think symbolically.

00:26:50.773 --> 00:26:52.940 align:middle line:84%
We know in ancient times--
we go right back to time,

00:26:52.940 --> 00:26:54.110 align:middle line:90%
everything was symbolic.

00:26:54.110 --> 00:26:56.360 align:middle line:90%
We thought in that deep--

00:26:56.360 --> 00:26:57.530 align:middle line:90%
nothing was on the surface.

00:26:57.530 --> 00:26:59.720 align:middle line:84%
It was always
underneath the surface.

00:26:59.720 --> 00:27:02.870 align:middle line:84%
We've lost that ability
over time to-- we

00:27:02.870 --> 00:27:04.410 align:middle line:84%
take things so
much at face value.

00:27:04.410 --> 00:27:06.680 align:middle line:84%
We don't look for the
layers underneath.

00:27:06.680 --> 00:27:08.330 align:middle line:84%
So my dream dictionaries
are basically

00:27:08.330 --> 00:27:10.160 align:middle line:84%
to kick start that
part of your brain,

00:27:10.160 --> 00:27:13.587 align:middle line:84%
that intuitive, brainstorming,
creative part, which

00:27:13.587 --> 00:27:15.920 align:middle line:84%
is where all great innovation
and discovery in the world

00:27:15.920 --> 00:27:16.310 align:middle line:90%
begins.

00:27:16.310 --> 00:27:18.020 align:middle line:84%
Did you know that
many scientists--

00:27:18.020 --> 00:27:19.880 align:middle line:84%
Einstein was a
very vivid dreamer.

00:27:19.880 --> 00:27:20.970 align:middle line:90%
The theory of relativity--

00:27:20.970 --> 00:27:21.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:27:21.770 --> 00:27:24.050 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --speed of light,
all inspired by a dream.

00:27:24.050 --> 00:27:25.610 align:middle line:90%
The periodic table, a dream.

00:27:25.610 --> 00:27:28.340 align:middle line:84%
Even Google was
inspired by a dream.

00:27:28.340 --> 00:27:31.340 align:middle line:84%
Now all our lives have
been changed by Google.

00:27:31.340 --> 00:27:33.208 align:middle line:84%
Larry Page was at
Stanford University

00:27:33.208 --> 00:27:35.000 align:middle line:84%
not knowing quite what
to do with his life.

00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:37.230 align:middle line:90%
He felt like he didn't fit in.

00:27:37.230 --> 00:27:38.682 align:middle line:84%
He was passionate
about computers.

00:27:38.682 --> 00:27:40.140 align:middle line:84%
He had a lot lying
around his room.

00:27:40.140 --> 00:27:41.540 align:middle line:84%
He went to bed
one night and then

00:27:41.540 --> 00:27:44.750 align:middle line:84%
had a dream that
all the information

00:27:44.750 --> 00:27:47.300 align:middle line:84%
from these computers could
be downloaded on one page.

00:27:47.300 --> 00:27:49.460 align:middle line:84%
He got up at 2:00
or 3:00 AM, which

00:27:49.460 --> 00:27:51.020 align:middle line:90%
I say is a very sacred time--

00:27:51.020 --> 00:27:52.160 align:middle line:90%
I can explain that--

00:27:52.160 --> 00:27:53.030 align:middle line:90%
did some math.

00:27:53.030 --> 00:27:54.020 align:middle line:90%
This could be possible.

00:27:54.020 --> 00:27:55.220 align:middle line:90%
Dropped out of Stanford.

00:27:55.220 --> 00:27:57.860 align:middle line:90%
Two years later created Google.

00:27:57.860 --> 00:28:02.000 align:middle line:84%
Like it or loathe it, Google
has changed our world.

00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:03.560 align:middle line:90%
And that started with a dream.

00:28:03.560 --> 00:28:04.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:28:04.520 --> 00:28:06.560 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about the
2:00 to 3:00 AM thing.

00:28:06.560 --> 00:28:07.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Yes.

00:28:07.490 --> 00:28:08.450 align:middle line:90%
Sacred.

00:28:08.450 --> 00:28:10.507 align:middle line:84%
If you wake up at 2:00
and 3:00 AM, most people--

00:28:10.507 --> 00:28:12.590 align:middle line:84%
I get so frustrated because
I see people who hate,

00:28:12.590 --> 00:28:13.520 align:middle line:90%
feel wrong.

00:28:13.520 --> 00:28:16.070 align:middle line:84%
They force themselves to go
to sleep, or they're anxious.

00:28:16.070 --> 00:28:17.360 align:middle line:90%
Don't celebrate it.

00:28:17.360 --> 00:28:19.430 align:middle line:84%
Your dreaming mind
has woken you up

00:28:19.430 --> 00:28:21.680 align:middle line:84%
because something
in your dream is

00:28:21.680 --> 00:28:24.620 align:middle line:84%
so important it wants you to
write it down and reflect.

00:28:24.620 --> 00:28:26.030 align:middle line:90%
Now I spent time--

00:28:26.030 --> 00:28:28.550 align:middle line:84%
before university,
actually, I wanted to go--

00:28:28.550 --> 00:28:30.290 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to be the
first female vicar.

00:28:30.290 --> 00:28:32.870 align:middle line:84%
I was very deep into
that, and I spent time

00:28:32.870 --> 00:28:33.920 align:middle line:90%
considering my options.

00:28:33.920 --> 00:28:36.140 align:middle line:84%
And I know that
the call to prayer

00:28:36.140 --> 00:28:39.350 align:middle line:84%
is early, is
between two and six.

00:28:39.350 --> 00:28:41.340 align:middle line:90%
It's a very sacred time.

00:28:41.340 --> 00:28:43.970 align:middle line:84%
And if you look at some of the
great innovators in the world,

00:28:43.970 --> 00:28:46.940 align:middle line:84%
most of their discoveries
and their eureka moments

00:28:46.940 --> 00:28:49.317 align:middle line:84%
are very in those
sacred early times.

00:28:49.317 --> 00:28:50.525 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So if you wake up--

00:28:50.525 --> 00:28:50.840 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Write it down.

00:28:50.840 --> 00:28:52.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --and you don't
know why at 2:00, 3:00,

00:28:52.370 --> 00:28:54.560 align:middle line:84%
4:00 in the morning, don't
beat yourself up, squeeze

00:28:54.560 --> 00:28:57.185 align:middle line:84%
your eyes shut, and say, I have
to go back to sleep right away.

00:28:57.185 --> 00:28:57.440 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Write it down--

00:28:57.440 --> 00:28:58.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Maybe take
a moment and say--

00:28:58.550 --> 00:28:58.895 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: --what's on your mind.

00:28:58.895 --> 00:28:59.120 align:middle line:90%
Write it down.

00:28:59.120 --> 00:28:59.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --what was going on?

00:28:59.960 --> 00:29:00.980 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Just journal away.

00:29:00.980 --> 00:29:03.440 align:middle line:84%
And it may change the world,
or it may change your life.

00:29:03.440 --> 00:29:06.290 align:middle line:84%
Both, to me, are
just as important.

00:29:06.290 --> 00:29:07.220 align:middle line:90%
Your life is just--

00:29:07.220 --> 00:29:08.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The problem
for a lot of people,

00:29:08.240 --> 00:29:09.260 align:middle line:90%
they're in a relationship.

00:29:09.260 --> 00:29:10.610 align:middle line:90%
And you think, how do I do this?

00:29:10.610 --> 00:29:12.410 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to wake
my partner up if I

00:29:12.410 --> 00:29:13.820 align:middle line:90%
turn the light on and do this.

00:29:13.820 --> 00:29:16.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's a big one for
when it comes to journaling.

00:29:16.790 --> 00:29:18.060 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: That is a big one.

00:29:18.060 --> 00:29:18.860 align:middle line:90%
I agree.

00:29:18.860 --> 00:29:19.905 align:middle line:90%
It is a big one.

00:29:19.905 --> 00:29:22.280 align:middle line:84%
You've got to be respectful,
but I think creep out of bed

00:29:22.280 --> 00:29:24.607 align:middle line:84%
and go to the
bathroom, sit down.

00:29:24.607 --> 00:29:26.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So keep your
journal next to the toilet.

00:29:26.690 --> 00:29:27.655 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:29:27.655 --> 00:29:28.780 align:middle line:90%
OK, that's a good solution.

00:29:28.780 --> 00:29:30.155 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Yeah,
and write it down

00:29:30.155 --> 00:29:32.535 align:middle line:84%
because you will be surprised
if you keep a journal.

00:29:32.535 --> 00:29:34.160 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Oscar Wilde
once said, I always

00:29:34.160 --> 00:29:36.530 align:middle line:84%
must have something sensational
to read on the train

00:29:36.530 --> 00:29:37.610 align:middle line:90%
so I bring my diary.

00:29:37.610 --> 00:29:41.480 align:middle line:84%
I say bring your dream diary
because you will see over time,

00:29:41.480 --> 00:29:44.180 align:middle line:84%
the dream diary is
commenting on your life.

00:29:44.180 --> 00:29:46.760 align:middle line:84%
It's like this avatar,
this other world,

00:29:46.760 --> 00:29:49.430 align:middle line:84%
that is commenting on
your everyday life.

00:29:49.430 --> 00:29:51.110 align:middle line:90%
It's utterly fascinating.

00:29:51.110 --> 00:29:53.390 align:middle line:84%
You will see precognitive
elements in your dreams.

00:29:53.390 --> 00:29:55.490 align:middle line:84%
You will see that
sense of deja vu.

00:29:55.490 --> 00:29:56.390 align:middle line:90%
I dreamt this.

00:29:56.390 --> 00:29:59.570 align:middle line:84%
You will see marvelous
symbols giving you

00:29:59.570 --> 00:30:02.690 align:middle line:84%
insight that can help you
move forward with your life.

00:30:02.690 --> 00:30:05.540 align:middle line:84%
You will see your dreaming
mind constantly trying

00:30:05.540 --> 00:30:08.360 align:middle line:84%
to guide, and inspire,
and enlighten you.

00:30:08.360 --> 00:30:11.580 align:middle line:84%
It's incredible, but you've
got to stick with it.

00:30:11.580 --> 00:30:13.108 align:middle line:90%
There's no point just doing one.

00:30:13.108 --> 00:30:15.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, you just give
us a very, very, very practical

00:30:15.650 --> 00:30:16.450 align:middle line:90%
solution.

00:30:16.450 --> 00:30:18.590 align:middle line:84%
If you're in partnership,
keep your journal

00:30:18.590 --> 00:30:20.270 align:middle line:84%
next to the toilet,
somewhere where

00:30:20.270 --> 00:30:22.760 align:middle line:84%
you can go and not
disturb the other person

00:30:22.760 --> 00:30:23.820 align:middle line:90%
with light at night.

00:30:23.820 --> 00:30:24.620 align:middle line:90%
I'm serious.

00:30:24.620 --> 00:30:29.078 align:middle line:84%
That's an excellent idea because
I wake up and think, oh--

00:30:29.078 --> 00:30:30.120 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Can't wake him.

00:30:30.120 --> 00:30:31.703 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --I want
to write this down,

00:30:31.703 --> 00:30:33.720 align:middle line:84%
and then I go back
to sleep and forget.

00:30:33.720 --> 00:30:33.980 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:30:33.980 --> 00:30:34.220 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: You will.

00:30:34.220 --> 00:30:35.637 align:middle line:84%
You must write it
down immediately

00:30:35.637 --> 00:30:37.345 align:middle line:84%
because the dreaming
mind comes--

00:30:37.345 --> 00:30:38.720 align:middle line:84%
the images in the
dream mind come

00:30:38.720 --> 00:30:40.720 align:middle line:84%
from the world of the
unconscious, which is very

00:30:40.720 --> 00:30:42.020 align:middle line:90%
subtle, intuition and subtle.

00:30:42.020 --> 00:30:45.500 align:middle line:84%
And it cannot compete
with rational reason ego,

00:30:45.500 --> 00:30:48.830 align:middle line:84%
which is ruled during-- that's
why dreams are so beautiful

00:30:48.830 --> 00:30:52.070 align:middle line:84%
because they're what your
intuition notices in the day

00:30:52.070 --> 00:30:55.350 align:middle line:84%
but your ego, or your reason,
or your logic just squash.

00:30:55.350 --> 00:30:56.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:30:56.150 --> 00:30:57.080 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:30:57.080 --> 00:30:58.370 align:middle line:90%
Let's go to deja vu.

00:30:58.370 --> 00:31:01.970 align:middle line:84%
You just brought it up a moment
ago because that is, I think,

00:31:01.970 --> 00:31:06.050 align:middle line:84%
a fascinating subject and
also much misunderstood

00:31:06.050 --> 00:31:08.477 align:middle line:84%
because sometimes
you're simply--

00:31:08.477 --> 00:31:09.560 align:middle line:90%
you've been there already.

00:31:09.560 --> 00:31:10.580 align:middle line:90%
You're practicing.

00:31:10.580 --> 00:31:12.755 align:middle line:84%
Talk about the
implications of deja vu.

00:31:12.755 --> 00:31:15.680 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Oh, the
implications are astonishing.

00:31:15.680 --> 00:31:18.200 align:middle line:84%
I truly believe now, in all
this research I've done--

00:31:18.200 --> 00:31:20.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I started
way back in 2000,

00:31:20.900 --> 00:31:22.580 align:middle line:84%
the psychological
element of dreams,

00:31:22.580 --> 00:31:23.930 align:middle line:90%
and I went to the spiritual.

00:31:23.930 --> 00:31:27.020 align:middle line:84%
And now I'm thinking all dreams
have a precognitive element.

00:31:27.020 --> 00:31:28.775 align:middle line:84%
We just haven't
seen them play out

00:31:28.775 --> 00:31:31.400 align:middle line:84%
because when we write them down,
the future hasn't happened yet

00:31:31.400 --> 00:31:33.470 align:middle line:84%
for us in real time,
so we don't know.

00:31:33.470 --> 00:31:34.310 align:middle line:90%
So pay attention.

00:31:34.310 --> 00:31:37.610 align:middle line:84%
I think all dreams have a
hint about a potential future

00:31:37.610 --> 00:31:40.680 align:middle line:90%
there for you that plays out.

00:31:40.680 --> 00:31:43.340 align:middle line:84%
And I think that happens every
single night in your dreams,

00:31:43.340 --> 00:31:46.820 align:middle line:84%
that you have an inkling
of a potential future.

00:31:46.820 --> 00:31:48.560 align:middle line:90%
And that is so exciting.

00:31:48.560 --> 00:31:50.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And sometimes
people do gather together,

00:31:50.810 --> 00:31:54.320 align:middle line:84%
and you do start practicing
things that you do

00:31:54.320 --> 00:31:55.650 align:middle line:90%
want to do in dream time.

00:31:55.650 --> 00:31:56.450 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Yes.

00:31:56.450 --> 00:31:57.110 align:middle line:90%
Yes, you do.

00:31:57.110 --> 00:31:59.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that
practice, once it happens,

00:31:59.060 --> 00:32:00.477 align:middle line:84%
I've already been here,
and I've already-- you

00:32:00.477 --> 00:32:01.550 align:middle line:90%
have already been there.

00:32:01.550 --> 00:32:02.630 align:middle line:90%
You have already done it.

00:32:02.630 --> 00:32:04.940 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Well, it shows that
there's a part of us, as I say,

00:32:04.940 --> 00:32:06.565 align:middle line:84%
call it consciousness,
spirit, or soul,

00:32:06.565 --> 00:32:09.800 align:middle line:84%
that exists independent
of our brain and our body.

00:32:09.800 --> 00:32:15.438 align:middle line:84%
Something has an awareness of
our future or our greater self.

00:32:15.438 --> 00:32:16.730 align:middle line:90%
Again, it's looking out for us.

00:32:16.730 --> 00:32:18.290 align:middle line:90%
It's giving us hints and tips.

00:32:18.290 --> 00:32:20.145 align:middle line:84%
And as I said, I
did a book called

00:32:20.145 --> 00:32:21.770 align:middle line:84%
"The Premonition
Code," where we looked

00:32:21.770 --> 00:32:23.150 align:middle line:90%
into the physics of time.

00:32:23.150 --> 00:32:25.280 align:middle line:84%
Scientists don't know
what sleep or dreams are.

00:32:25.280 --> 00:32:26.870 align:middle line:84%
They don't know
what time is either.

00:32:26.870 --> 00:32:29.060 align:middle line:84%
There are all these experiments
showing that the future can

00:32:29.060 --> 00:32:29.860 align:middle line:90%
influence the past.

00:32:29.860 --> 00:32:31.700 align:middle line:84%
The past can
influence the future.

00:32:31.700 --> 00:32:34.220 align:middle line:90%
It is so fascinating.

00:32:34.220 --> 00:32:36.620 align:middle line:84%
But in our dream world,
I think it's a doorway.

00:32:36.620 --> 00:32:39.225 align:middle line:84%
It's the entry point
to this spiritual world

00:32:39.225 --> 00:32:41.600 align:middle line:84%
and this timelessness because
when you go into the dream,

00:32:41.600 --> 00:32:44.220 align:middle line:84%
time and space
doesn't exist anymore.

00:32:44.220 --> 00:32:45.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:32:45.020 --> 00:32:49.268 align:middle line:84%
It can seem like you've had an
entire dramatic play play out,

00:32:49.268 --> 00:32:50.435 align:middle line:90%
and it's been a few seconds.

00:32:50.435 --> 00:32:52.737 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Yeah, and that's
why afterlife dreams

00:32:52.737 --> 00:32:53.570 align:middle line:90%
can be very healing.

00:32:53.570 --> 00:32:55.820 align:middle line:84%
And especially, again, to
reference the pandemic,

00:32:55.820 --> 00:32:59.360 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people had dreams of
meeting departed loved ones,

00:32:59.360 --> 00:33:00.990 align:middle line:84%
and these dreams
were very healing.

00:33:00.990 --> 00:33:03.740 align:middle line:84%
There is research to
show that in around 90%

00:33:03.740 --> 00:33:06.710 align:middle line:84%
of cases, people who have an
afterlife dream, that means

00:33:06.710 --> 00:33:08.600 align:middle line:84%
that they have a
conversation in their dreams

00:33:08.600 --> 00:33:11.120 align:middle line:84%
with someone who's departed,
actually deal better

00:33:11.120 --> 00:33:13.010 align:middle line:90%
with the grieving process.

00:33:13.010 --> 00:33:14.320 align:middle line:90%
Is it an afterlife sign?

00:33:14.320 --> 00:33:15.120 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:33:15.120 --> 00:33:16.328 align:middle line:90%
I don't know all the answers.

00:33:16.328 --> 00:33:17.690 align:middle line:90%
Potentially, it could be.

00:33:17.690 --> 00:33:18.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:33:18.530 --> 00:33:21.600 align:middle line:84%
And with this audience, they'd
be very comfortable with that.

00:33:21.600 --> 00:33:23.310 align:middle line:84%
OK, you're bringing
to mind something I

00:33:23.310 --> 00:33:24.560 align:middle line:90%
hadn't planned on bringing up.

00:33:24.560 --> 00:33:25.520 align:middle line:90%
It just popped in.

00:33:25.520 --> 00:33:29.010 align:middle line:84%
A friend of mine, who
is also a very talented,

00:33:29.010 --> 00:33:32.360 align:middle line:84%
very adept channeler-- and I
don't use that word lightly--

00:33:32.360 --> 00:33:36.500 align:middle line:84%
a real one, very sensitive
and dreams a lot too--

00:33:36.500 --> 00:33:39.140 align:middle line:84%
so we all get together
with this group of people

00:33:39.140 --> 00:33:41.240 align:middle line:84%
through this strange
situation-- it

00:33:41.240 --> 00:33:42.950 align:middle line:84%
all came together
at the last minute--

00:33:42.950 --> 00:33:46.490 align:middle line:84%
and all end up with this
strange man on a vision quest.

00:33:46.490 --> 00:33:47.420 align:middle line:90%
No one planned it.

00:33:47.420 --> 00:33:48.260 align:middle line:90%
It just happened.

00:33:48.260 --> 00:33:50.660 align:middle line:90%
This is in real life.

00:33:50.660 --> 00:33:53.180 align:middle line:90%
We get to her son's house.

00:33:53.180 --> 00:33:56.570 align:middle line:84%
And she's saying, well, maybe
our son will let us stay there.

00:33:56.570 --> 00:33:57.900 align:middle line:90%
My son will let us stay there.

00:33:57.900 --> 00:33:58.910 align:middle line:90%
So we go and stay there.

00:33:58.910 --> 00:34:01.370 align:middle line:84%
And the leader of
the pack is kind

00:34:01.370 --> 00:34:03.710 align:middle line:84%
of taking advantage, eating
the food in the refrigerator

00:34:03.710 --> 00:34:06.230 align:middle line:84%
and really making a
nuisance of himself.

00:34:06.230 --> 00:34:08.630 align:middle line:84%
And so she kept
apologizing to her son.

00:34:08.630 --> 00:34:10.190 align:middle line:90%
This is the interesting part.

00:34:10.190 --> 00:34:13.860 align:middle line:84%
I am so sorry we did
this to you again.

00:34:13.860 --> 00:34:15.659 align:middle line:84%
And he said, what are
you talking about?

00:34:15.659 --> 00:34:18.110 align:middle line:84%
She said, well, the last time
I brought all these people.

00:34:18.110 --> 00:34:20.600 align:middle line:84%
I am so sorry we did
this to you again.

00:34:20.600 --> 00:34:21.870 align:middle line:90%
I'll never do this again.

00:34:21.870 --> 00:34:24.900 align:middle line:84%
And he said, mom, you've
never done this before.

00:34:24.900 --> 00:34:28.400 align:middle line:84%
So later, she goes, and
she's talking to her guide.

00:34:28.400 --> 00:34:29.699 align:middle line:90%
We're talking to her guide.

00:34:29.699 --> 00:34:32.179 align:middle line:84%
They said, well, you
have, but you all

00:34:32.179 --> 00:34:34.610 align:middle line:84%
got together and practiced
this in dream time.

00:34:34.610 --> 00:34:37.027 align:middle line:84%
And she was thinking
that it was real life.

00:34:37.027 --> 00:34:38.735 align:middle line:84%
She couldn't tell the
difference anymore.

00:34:38.735 --> 00:34:40.670 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Remarkable, isn't it?

00:34:40.670 --> 00:34:42.280 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I love that.

00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:44.280 align:middle line:84%
I think it's "Inception,"
or is it "The Matrix?"

00:34:44.280 --> 00:34:45.159 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:34:45.159 --> 00:34:46.909 align:middle line:84%
These dream-inspired
movies, have you ever

00:34:46.909 --> 00:34:48.949 align:middle line:84%
had a dream that was
so real that it's only

00:34:48.949 --> 00:34:51.210 align:middle line:84%
when you wake up that you
thought it was a dream?

00:34:51.210 --> 00:34:52.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:34:52.010 --> 00:34:52.250 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:34:52.250 --> 00:34:52.820 align:middle line:90%
All the time.

00:34:52.820 --> 00:34:53.695 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Incredible.

00:34:53.695 --> 00:34:57.320 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I'm so
passionate about this.

00:34:57.320 --> 00:34:59.252 align:middle line:90%
And science can't explain it.

00:34:59.252 --> 00:35:00.335 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, they cannot.

00:35:00.335 --> 00:35:01.880 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: But these stories--

00:35:01.880 --> 00:35:02.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They can't
explain consciousness.

00:35:02.930 --> 00:35:03.620 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: No.

00:35:03.620 --> 00:35:04.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So there you go.

00:35:04.340 --> 00:35:05.715 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: They're
trying, though.

00:35:05.715 --> 00:35:09.680 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole emerging
breed of scientists.

00:35:09.680 --> 00:35:12.050 align:middle line:84%
And I actually have worked
quite closely with them

00:35:12.050 --> 00:35:14.000 align:middle line:90%
for the last six years.

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:17.420 align:middle line:84%
I support them, do
webinars with them,

00:35:17.420 --> 00:35:19.070 align:middle line:84%
co-authored a book
with one of them.

00:35:19.070 --> 00:35:23.690 align:middle line:84%
The science of consciousness is
a really exciting emerging area

00:35:23.690 --> 00:35:26.630 align:middle line:84%
that science is willing to go
there now and show that science

00:35:26.630 --> 00:35:27.890 align:middle line:90%
and spirit are actually--

00:35:27.890 --> 00:35:28.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it's starting.

00:35:28.730 --> 00:35:29.600 align:middle line:90%
Definitely starting.

00:35:29.600 --> 00:35:29.900 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: It's starting.

00:35:29.900 --> 00:35:31.775 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They don't
have it nailed down yet,

00:35:31.775 --> 00:35:33.643 align:middle line:90%
but they'll get there over time.

00:35:33.643 --> 00:35:35.060 align:middle line:84%
OK, one thing I
want to talk about

00:35:35.060 --> 00:35:37.550 align:middle line:84%
is a lot of people
say, A, I don't dream.

00:35:37.550 --> 00:35:38.730 align:middle line:90%
They're not dreaming.

00:35:38.730 --> 00:35:39.530 align:middle line:90%
They're forgetting.

00:35:39.530 --> 00:35:40.580 align:middle line:90%
They're not remembering.

00:35:40.580 --> 00:35:43.910 align:middle line:84%
So let's give people
a couple little tips

00:35:43.910 --> 00:35:45.975 align:middle line:84%
on how we can start
recalling dreams because--

00:35:45.975 --> 00:35:46.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CHEUNG: Absolutely.

00:35:46.850 --> 00:35:49.910 align:middle line:84%
Brain scans show that we
dream every single night,

00:35:49.910 --> 00:35:51.800 align:middle line:84%
and you have at least
five or six dreams.

00:35:51.800 --> 00:35:53.150 align:middle line:90%
You're just not recalling them.

00:35:53.150 --> 00:35:55.230 align:middle line:90%
And that could be for a reason.

00:35:55.230 --> 00:35:57.500 align:middle line:84%
You're probably very, very
busy, and preoccupied,

00:35:57.500 --> 00:35:59.060 align:middle line:84%
and very immersed
in the material

00:35:59.060 --> 00:36:00.210 align:middle line:90%
world in your waking life.

00:36:00.210 --> 00:36:03.870 align:middle line:84%
You could also be someone with a
very logical, rational mindset.

00:36:03.870 --> 00:36:06.440 align:middle line:84%
And if you-- the story you've
told yourself all your life is

00:36:06.440 --> 00:36:09.050 align:middle line:84%
that dreams are meaningless--
we're taught that from an early

00:36:09.050 --> 00:36:12.050 align:middle line:84%
age, and I'm on a mission
to overthrow that--

00:36:12.050 --> 00:36:14.210 align:middle line:84%
of course, you're not
going to remember it

00:36:14.210 --> 00:36:17.580 align:middle line:84%
because your reason and your
logic are overriding it.

00:36:17.580 --> 00:36:19.750 align:middle line:84%
So the first tip is
to pay more attention

00:36:19.750 --> 00:36:22.300 align:middle line:84%
to the possibility of dreams
because like anything in life,

00:36:22.300 --> 00:36:24.550 align:middle line:84%
you're dreaming mind is
crying out for your attention.

00:36:24.550 --> 00:36:27.100 align:middle line:84%
And where your attention goes,
that's where the reward is.

00:36:27.100 --> 00:36:30.430 align:middle line:84%
I predict people watching
this will dream tonight

00:36:30.430 --> 00:36:31.497 align:middle line:90%
because they're thinking.

00:36:31.497 --> 00:36:33.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They'll remember
their dreams, you mean.

00:36:33.580 --> 00:36:35.050 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: Yeah, well,
they will remember it.

00:36:35.050 --> 00:36:36.550 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, they will dream, and
they will recall them--

00:36:36.550 --> 00:36:37.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
they'll recall them.

00:36:37.120 --> 00:36:39.290 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: --because their
attention during the day

00:36:39.290 --> 00:36:40.090 align:middle line:90%
has diverted it.

00:36:40.090 --> 00:36:43.420 align:middle line:84%
So you've got to start actually
taking dreams seriously.

00:36:43.420 --> 00:36:45.250 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure your
audience will anyway.

00:36:45.250 --> 00:36:48.160 align:middle line:84%
But you've also got to start
not just taking them seriously

00:36:48.160 --> 00:36:50.530 align:middle line:84%
but to think they have
something of value to teach me.

00:36:50.530 --> 00:36:55.090 align:middle line:84%
Your attitude to dream life is
key in whether you recall it.

00:36:55.090 --> 00:36:57.250 align:middle line:84%
Number two, are you
getting enough REM sleep?

00:36:57.250 --> 00:36:59.050 align:middle line:84%
If you're not having
a good night's sleep

00:36:59.050 --> 00:37:01.390 align:middle line:84%
and your bedroom isn't
a very relaxing place,

00:37:01.390 --> 00:37:03.010 align:middle line:90%
that's not going to help.

00:37:03.010 --> 00:37:06.140 align:middle line:84%
Number three, are you
writing down your dreams?

00:37:06.140 --> 00:37:09.040 align:middle line:84%
Even if something comes up
like a bicycle in the morning,

00:37:09.040 --> 00:37:11.350 align:middle line:84%
even if it's just a random
word, write it down.

00:37:11.350 --> 00:37:14.260 align:middle line:84%
The very act of writing it down
will prompt your dreaming mind

00:37:14.260 --> 00:37:16.450 align:middle line:84%
the next morning because
we are creatures of habit.

00:37:16.450 --> 00:37:18.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're conditioning
yourself to remember then.

00:37:18.880 --> 00:37:19.135 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:37:19.135 --> 00:37:21.340 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: The key thing,
though, is the first 90 seconds

00:37:21.340 --> 00:37:22.090 align:middle line:90%
when you wake up.

00:37:22.090 --> 00:37:23.560 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people do
everything which

00:37:23.560 --> 00:37:25.480 align:middle line:84%
is the total opposite
of what they should do.

00:37:25.480 --> 00:37:26.650 align:middle line:90%
You've got to keep still.

00:37:26.650 --> 00:37:28.450 align:middle line:84%
So if you wake up in
the fetal position,

00:37:28.450 --> 00:37:30.940 align:middle line:84%
stay in that position
just for 90 seconds or so.

00:37:30.940 --> 00:37:33.620 align:middle line:84%
Keep your eyes closed because
as soon as you wake it up,

00:37:33.620 --> 00:37:36.880 align:middle line:90%
you jet it into waking life.

00:37:36.880 --> 00:37:39.460 align:middle line:84%
Ideally, also, wake up
without an alarm clock

00:37:39.460 --> 00:37:41.080 align:middle line:84%
because an alarm
clock is too brutal.

00:37:41.080 --> 00:37:44.380 align:middle line:84%
Try and wake up naturally,
and just stay in that position

00:37:44.380 --> 00:37:46.570 align:middle line:84%
because any physical
movement will put you

00:37:46.570 --> 00:37:47.920 align:middle line:90%
into the waking world.

00:37:47.920 --> 00:37:50.890 align:middle line:84%
Stay in that position and
just see what dreams may come.

00:37:50.890 --> 00:37:54.270 align:middle line:84%
If nothing comes, recall the
feeling because that feeling--

00:37:54.270 --> 00:37:56.020 align:middle line:84%
we all wake up feeling
slightly different.

00:37:56.020 --> 00:37:57.645 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we're more
happy than others.

00:37:57.645 --> 00:38:00.220 align:middle line:84%
That would often be as
a result of the dream.

00:38:00.220 --> 00:38:01.210 align:middle line:90%
And write it down.

00:38:01.210 --> 00:38:03.880 align:middle line:84%
Again, the action
of writing it down

00:38:03.880 --> 00:38:05.770 align:middle line:84%
sends a message to your
dreaming mind, look,

00:38:05.770 --> 00:38:07.190 align:middle line:90%
she's taking me seriously.

00:38:07.190 --> 00:38:07.990 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I'm excited.

00:38:07.990 --> 00:38:09.610 align:middle line:84%
It's like someone who's
been texting you for years

00:38:09.610 --> 00:38:11.140 align:middle line:84%
and trying to get
a date, and then--

00:38:11.140 --> 00:38:11.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:38:11.480 --> 00:38:13.600 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: [LAUGHS] --and
then they're noticing me.

00:38:13.600 --> 00:38:14.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm excited.

00:38:14.020 --> 00:38:14.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:38:14.820 --> 00:38:17.470 align:middle line:84%
>>CHEUNG: I'm going to send an
amazing dream the next night.

00:38:17.470 --> 00:38:20.020 align:middle line:84%
During the day also,
do some reality checks.

00:38:20.020 --> 00:38:21.485 align:middle line:90%
Ask yourself, is this a dream?

00:38:21.485 --> 00:38:22.360 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I don't know.

00:38:22.360 --> 00:38:24.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Everything you're
saying is I think a thought,

00:38:24.970 --> 00:38:27.250 align:middle line:84%
and then you're talking
about that the next second.

00:38:27.250 --> 00:38:28.750 align:middle line:84%
So I don't have to
ask you anything.

00:38:28.750 --> 00:38:29.360 align:middle line:90%
Go for it.

